Title: Corpse Princess: The Complete Series

reviewText: I went through this set in less than a week, often watching a disc a day, which is a reflection of the program's entertainment value. I'm a "Ghost in The Shell" fan and enjoy programs that fall along those lines. I found this set to have pretty good video quality for standard DVD. The only tiresome item was that "Shikabane Hime" must have been said dozens of times each episode...at least it seemed that way. Good dub, good story line. No weird Japanese ending. Any anime fan should really like this one.
Title: Corpse Princess: The Complete Series

reviewText: I recently bought Corpse Princess: The Complete Series S.A.V.E from walmart.com. The set was a great deal since in 2008 had first seen the series when FUNimation posted it up on Youtube and always thought it had a great unique story, superb animation (By Studio Gainax), and the soundtrack was amazing too considering its performed by angela. When you buy this the video quality is high too. Crisp and clear which included two extras of voice actor's commentary.This a must-get dvd set.
summary: Corpse Princess SAVE Edition great quality

Title: Corpse Princess: The Complete Series

reviewText: Corpse Princess has an open ending, meaning you can be satisfied, but there is room for more. This is not a bad thing. The characters are interesting, thier stories are unique, and there are a few surprises that I didn't predict. I won't get in to the details, but some relationships I felt should have developed a bit more, or differently. Other than that, this series had it's moments where you find yourself whishing on behalf of the characters. This is a good example of drawing the viewer into the story. All in all, some wholsem entertainment and good family fun.
summary: With a few changes, I would have loved it.

Title: Corpse Princess: The Complete Series

reviewText: I just finished the show and have mixed feelings.  Usually an anime will make me want more after its over but in the Corpse Princess I neither wanted more nor fast forwarded to to make the pain stop.  The artwork was good but not the best.  The story was interesting.  The series had more gore than I am used to and little fan service or humor.  The Corpse Princess was worth watching for the story but I don't think I would buy it to watch over and over.
Title: Corpse Princess: The Complete Series

reviewText: Though the story and setting seemed dark but made one think and ponder the subject of death. The characters seemed to grow with the story and plot and your able to relate to them on some level. We all experience death of family members and need a way to understand the reason behind the death. Thank you.
